\mt3 BaÍûâmoe Bukoeno Mabu Hawakalimi Tabo
\p BaÍûâmoe buka baÍûâ Aramia Tabo tawakalubino bukala, ibi mabumaÍûâ ale baÍûâmoi tabo komokomo tukulubino Baibolo bukane ohobaÍûâmidalimaÍûâ. BaÍûâgala kalakala konomola, baÍûâmoe atu tetelo ale Fly Tabo tawakalubino buka ibi mabumaÍûâ atumu beka-ododimaÍûâ. Buka kaÍûâlamiholedawa, amaÍûâle baÍûâmoe bukoeno hunu tabo baÍûâma kaÍûâna umaÍûâta, ‚ÄòGodokono Hido Tabo, Ebete Ebeno Uli Nopo TawakalubaÍûâtamo DaÍûâtamotiyaÍûâ.‚Äô
\p BaÍûâbemaÍûâ ale aeno konomo kalakala Godotamo adipatemaÍûâ, mabu ebeno malemale ipuwalo ebete ebeno ubi komo yaÍûâlo ihatiyaÍûâ baÍûâmoe hido komo Tabo tawakalubaÍûâtamo kododimaÍûâ. BaÍûâmoe baÍûâbe mabumaÍûâ 1987 gogolo tupuimiti, ebete komo hiyaÍûâhiyaÍûâ hibimaÍûâ midipino tepo ipuwoeno ukui ba wadiyaÍûâpaaÍûâlatele ibino toetoe tabo olamagimi komodo baÍûâgala ibino mani ikameho komodo atamo helo ikaaÍûâmenakui, ale baÍûâmoe oko hibinomolo kupulaÍûâmaÍûâ.
\p BaÍûâbemaÍûâ wadiyala Godote baÍûâmoe bukoeno oko owati komone konomo awagaha komo naÍûâlawenakamene, mabu hibila, ‚ÄúEbete genama ete oko owatihino, puyaÍûâte baÍûâbe oko owatimaÍûâ dewagelena ibaÍûâte hibi komo aÍûâkumaÍûâmenaÍûâ‚Äù (Ohale 127.1). BaÍûâbemaÍûâ kalakala konomola, Godote kebe oko yaÍûâlo daÍûâtupuimiyaÍûâ, ebete baÍûâbe hido oko ebeno Tabo tawakalubaÍûâgodolo ba owatina, wadiyala ibaÍûâte baÍûâmoe KaÍûâkaÍûâ Buka kaÍûâlamihole komodo baÍûâgala iyaÍûâtulame komodo ibino hibimaÍûâ midi ipuwalo kodakodanomomaÍûâ nedaÍûâhamenaÍûâ.
\mt3 English Preface
\p This book is a translation of the New Testament into the Aramia River dialect of the Tabo language of Papua New Guinea. It is being published simultaneously with the New Testament for the other half of the language, the speakers of the Fly River dialect. The two dialects together presently comprise a total of about 3,400 speakers, most of whom live in villages located along the banks of the Aramia, Bamu, and Fly Rivers as well as Segero Creek.
\p We offer thanks to God who out of love for the Tabo people determined to give them this special gift. We are grateful to Him for the many, many individuals who, by their faithfulness in prayer and giving over the years, have enabled us to complete this work. Through them God has caused this portion of His Word to become a reality for the Tabo people in their heart language.
\p And so we dedicate this book to God for his eternal glory, for truly, ‚ÄúUnless He builds the house, its builders labour in vain‚Äù (Psalm 127.1). May He use the reading and the teaching of this Book of Life to continue building His house among the Tabo people, helping them not only to grow as a church in terms of numbers, but also in an ever increasing quality of faith. 
